Carmichael. Although he formed a theory about whose gun launched
the fatal bullet, he's keeping it to himself. The shooting was
accidental, he says, the family would be hurt by such suspicions,
and it's pure speculation.
</P>
<P>
   Even a novelist can't take such liberties.
</P>
<P>
   To tell the story, Stuart invented two protagonists - young
attorney Billy Wade and his sweetheart, Mary Ann. Billy is all
fiction. The bright and feisty Mary Ann is based on Stuart's wife,
Kathleen.
</P>
<P>
   (beginitalic) (enditalic)Through Mary Ann and Billy's narration,
(beginitalic)The Gallup (enditalic)(beginitalic)14(enditalic) winds
its way leisurely through the events of 1935: First the eviction of
mine workers from company-owned housing, then the riot that
exploded in an alley. Ten men shot, more than 180 suspects jailed,
14 indicted, 10 brought to trial. Bigotry worked against those
arrested - most were Hispanic, many of them communists.
</P>
<P>
   Stuart modeled his writing style after the historic novels of
Irving Stone. He's also a fan of lawyers-turned-authors Scott Turow
and John Grisham, though not of the latter's depiction of lawyers,
which Stuart sees as unrelentingly negative.
</P>
<P>
   He spent 10 months of research and a year of writing while
working at his law firm full time. The University of New Mexico
Press published (beginitalic) Gallup (enditalic)(beginitalic)14
(enditalic)this March. Now the book(beginitalic) (enditalic)is the
talk of Gallup, where Stuart and his wife still spend much of their
time. A favorable review from the bookseller's bible,
(beginitalic)Pubisher's Weekly(enditalic), has brought inquiries
from Hollywood, though no deals have yet been struck.
</P>
<P>
   Stuart would welcome a movie contract but has heard horror
stories from other authors, including his friend, John Nichols, a
screenwriter and author of (beginitalic)The Milagro Beanfield
War(enditalic). Robert Redford turned that book into a 1988 movie.
</P>
<P>
   Nichols, burned by past deals that fell through, joked that he
will happily write the script for (beginitalic)The
(enditalic)(beginitalic)Gallup 14 (enditalic)''as soon as I get the
check.''
</P>
<P>
   Stuart has written two more novels - ``somewhat experimental'' -
since (beginitalic)The(enditalic)(beginitalic) Gallup 14(enditalic)
and has no plans to publish them. But he is eagerly pursuing his
