<DOCTYPE> MISCELLANEOUS TEXT (slug-filter) </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 10:58 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4888 &Cx1f; tad-z
r a BC-CONSUMERQ&AMP;A0627-COX     06-26 0905
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CONSUMERQ&AMP;A0627-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Consumer Q&AMP;A
 &HT;    By Jane Greig
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   Q: I would like to send a letter to former Lady Longhorn
basketball star Edwina Brown, who is currently playing in the WNBA
with the Detroit Shock, but I have been unable to locate an address
for the team. Could you provide an address for the Detroit Shock
organization?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.A.
</P>
<P>
   A: Selected third in the 2000 WNBA draft, Brown is enjoying her
stint with the Shock, scoring nine points in the team's opening
game this season. Write to her at 2 Championship Drive, Auburn
Hills, Mich. 48326.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have a relative who is going crazy because she can't find
out who sang the song on ``Providence'' when Syd was coming out of
her coma just as the show was ending.
</P>
<P>
   _ N.N.
</P>
<P>
   A: ``The Circle Game'' by Joni Mitchell on her ``Hits'' CD.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have some pure silver filigree jewelry from the Philippines
that has darkened a little. With what can I clean this?
</P>
<P>
   _ M. D.
</P>
<P>
   A: Do not use paper towels or tissue, which may scratch the
surface, or silver dips, which remove a bit of the silver along
with the tarnish, advises Rewards owner Claudia Stromberg. What
does this purveyor of silver jewelry recommend? Storing silver
jewelry in Pacific cloth and cleaning it with a soft cloth
containing a little polish. Want to try it?
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can we find the bags to make sandbags out of? We want
to be prepared in case of flooding.
</P>
<P>
   _ Diane Roberts
</P>
<P>
   A: This spurt of rain really has you worried. Sandbags divert
water but are not designed to seal out all water. Fill them about
half full and stack with the folded top face down. If exposed to
the elements for several months, a sandbag will deteriorate. Order
100 bags for $26 plus shipping from the Sacramento Bag Co. at (800)
287-BAGS. Burlap bags for sand are also available, but at twice the
cost. Sand is preferable, but sandbags work with most any kind of
top soil.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Could you please let me know how I can contact Jimmy Smits,
the actor from ``L.A. Law'' and big-screen movies? I was hoping to
send him an invitation to speak at our annual luncheon.
</P>
<P>
   _ R.G.
</P>
<P>
   A: There is always a chance. Write to this Brooklyn native at
Endeavor Talent Agency, c/o Adam Venit, 9701 Wilshire Blvd.,
Beverly Hills, Calif. 90212.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for pins that are commemorating the Olympics
this year.
</P>
<P>
   _ M. Sperle
</P>
<P>
   A: Order a pin by calling (800) 556-1998, or visit the United
States Olympic Committee at store.usoc.org.Prefer a catalog? E-mail
customer.service1(at) usoc.org. Pins range from $7 to $24.99. Spend
at least $50 and receive a free 2000 Olympics cap. All proceeds go
to the USOC, although only 35 cents of every dollar supports
athlete training.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Our cat decided to use our bed for a litter box. We have
tried vinegar/water and baking soda. We need help to get the smell
out.
</P>
<P>
   _ J.C.
</P>
<P>
   A: Club soda followed by corn starch works to remove pet stains
on carpet; however, mattresses are a vexing problem. Tilt the
mattress and try Nature's Miracle (available at PetsMart and PetCo
stores), which contains an enzyme solution designed to attack the
protein in the urine. Rinse and dry thoroughly. A spritz of vinegar
and water never hurts.
</P>
<P>
   Q: My son is turning 7, and every year I look for the same
birthday gift. Growing up in the 1970s, my sister and I looked
forward to watching ``The New Zoo Review'' with Doug and Emmy Jo
and the characters Freddie the frog, Charlie the owl and Henrietta
Hippo. Help me find any copies.
</P>
<P>
   _ Isabel Rivera
</P>
<P>
   A: Videos as well as boxed sets complete with zoo character
plush toys are sold by O. Atlas Enterprises in Ms. Goodbody's
Shoppe (a two-episode tape is sold separately for $9). Call (877)
782-3528 or visit www.newzoorevue.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: During the NHL finals, my brother and I placed a wager
regarding the Stanley Cup. He thinks they add a section to the Cup
as the years go by; thus, the trophy continues to grow. I think the
NHL has used several different Cups _ once one trophy is filled to
capacity, they purchase another trophy and begin to engrave the
players' names onto it. Who's right?
</P>
<P>
   _ Traci Cuellar
</P>
<P>
   A: Neither one of you. The original Stanley Cup Trophy (really a
bowl) is the oldest trophy for which professional athletes in North
America vie. It is named for Frederick Allen Lord Stanley of
Preston and is on display at the Hockey Hall of Fame in Toronto.
The current Stanley Cup, weighing in at 36 pounds and standing 35
1/4 inches high, adds and retires rings as necessary, says NHL
historian John Halligan. How else could the names of all those
players and teams fit? Now, a moment of silence for the Dallas
Stars.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I'm decorating a '60s/'70s room. Do you know where I can find
an old artifact called a color box? It hooks up to your stereo and
the colors change to the tempo and mood of the music.
</P>
<P>
   _ Frank Alterman
</P>
<P>
   A: Party like it's 1970. These nifty boxes are known as color
organs. To construct one, pick up an electronic kit ($25.90) from
Gibson Tech Ed Inc. at (800) 422-1100 or www.gibsonteched.net,or a
three-channel kit ($15) from Gateway Electronics at (800) 669-5810
or www.gatewayelex.com. Contact Jane Greig at P.O. Box 670, Austin,
TX 78767; (512) 445-3697; e-mail jgreig(at)statesman.com or fax
(512) 445-3968.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
