 &HT;    Consumer Q&AMP;A
 &HT;    By Jane Greig
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   Q: I would like to send a letter to former Lady Longhorn
basketball star Edwina Brown, who is currently playing in the WNBA
with the Detroit Shock, but I have been unable to locate an address
for the team. Could you provide an address for the Detroit Shock
organization?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.A.
</P>
<P>
   A: Selected third in the 2000 WNBA draft, Brown is enjoying her
stint with the Shock, scoring nine points in the team's opening
game this season. Write to her at 2 Championship Drive, Auburn
Hills, Mich. 48326.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have a relative who is going crazy because she can't find
out who sang the song on ``Providence'' when Syd was coming out of
her coma just as the show was ending.
</P>
<P>
   _ N.N.
</P>
<P>
   A: ``The Circle Game'' by Joni Mitchell on her ``Hits'' CD.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have some pure silver filigree jewelry from the Philippines
that has darkened a little. With what can I clean this?
</P>
<P>
   _ M. D.
</P>
<P>
   A: Do not use paper towels or tissue, which may scratch the
surface, or silver dips, which remove a bit of the silver along
with the tarnish, advises Rewards owner Claudia Stromberg. What
does this purveyor of silver jewelry recommend? Storing silver
jewelry in Pacific cloth and cleaning it with a soft cloth
containing a little polish. Want to try it?
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can we find the bags to make sandbags out of? We want
to be prepared in case of flooding.
