<SLUG> BC-TECH-PLAYGEAR0627-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    X marks the scope
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas
</P>
<P>
   Designed with sporting events, nature loving and people watching
in mind, Carson Optical's X-Scope ($23; www.carson-optical.com) is
a multi-purpose ``optical pocket tool'' for all your see-the-sights
needs. Its diminutive stature belies its six-function versatility
as a 30x power microscope (bug watcher), a 6x telescope (people
watcher) and a 3x foldout magnifier (up close and personal people
watcher). The X-scope also includes a wee flashlight, a signal
whistle, and directional compass. Not just a cheap novelty item,
the X-Scope's lenses are all glass, which ensures consistently
sharp, clear viewing with the passage of time. Two AAA batteries
not included.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
