</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Let questionaire help find city of your dreams
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   homes.wsj.com/d/best.html _ Sure, you love the city where you
live, but if the Wanderlust should hit, what city should you live
in next? This handy questionaire, which tabulates your responses to
questions about air quality, housing costs and unemployment rates,
will tell you what cities are best suited to you, ranking them in
order.
</P>
<P>
   www.finalfantasy.com _ ``Final Fantasy'' has gone from a humble
console game to a gorgeous, multimedia work of art as a series of
games on the Sony Playstation. Now, ``Final Fantasy'' is gearing up
for movie screens with a full-length compute-animated movie to
debut next year. For now, check out the concept art and fantastic
short trailers that are updated weekly on the site.
www.bestweb.net/(tilde)hmcnally/shaft/ _ We love Samuel L.
Jackson's take on ``Shaft,'' but there will always be a place in
our hearts for the hard-hitting lines delivered by Richard
Roundtree in the original 1971 movie. This site has samples of some
sounds from all three original Shaft movies, from Rountree's
delivery of ``Stay loose, baby,'' to ``Don't jive me!'' A good way
to increase self-confidence in the privacy of your own cubicle.
</P>
<P>
   www.tdcj.state.tx.us/stat/finalmeals.htm _ It's morbid,
disturbing and very compelling. Texas' Department of Criminal
Justice and its frequent execution of, well, executions has
produced this interesting bit of anecdotal data: a list of
requested last meals by death row inmates. From breaded pork chops
with all the trimmings to salmon croquettes, see what was on the
menu for these doomed prisoners
</P>
