 &HT;    News for kids
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   abcnews4kids.com _ This brand new interactive news site offers
important world and national news with animated graphics, audio and
text. It repackages the news in a way that is meant to be appealing
to children. The language isn't watered down, but the material is
presented in short bursts, to hold a short attention span. Each
news story includes a search box that enables users to search the
Web site of Encyclopedia Britannica.
</P>
<P>
   www.barbie.com _ Barbie isn't just about a plastic doll anymore.
The timeless girls' toy has a Web site that includes a daily poll
(recent questions: ``Boy bands: how do they rate?'' and ``Pokemon:
your favorite is:'') a Barbie postcard messenger service and
personality quiz, not to mention several pages that feature Barbies
to order online. There is even a product line called Barbie
Software for Girls. Check out the feature Barbie for President.
This Barbie wears a smart, royal blue suit with campaign button and
hairdo that closely resembles that of a certain U.S. Senate
candidate in New York. Learn about Barbie's platform for the 2000
election and read brief sketches of real-life women politicians.
</P>
