   c. 2000 Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Driving to work, I often make mental lists of all my
mistakes. I could drive to Oregon and back and still not get bored.
</P>
<P>
   For instance, there was the time, at 23, when I bought a $29.95
wig at J.C. Penney with the conviction it would forever change my
life. It did. I looked so weird _ very much like I was wearing a
dead possum _ that I had to move from my native Arkansas in shame.
</P>
<P>
   I haven't done much better with my high-tech predictions.
</P>
<P>
   There was my fearless pronouncement, years ago, that AOL would
soon bite the dust. AOL not only stayed around, it's the world's
largest ISP. Then there was the column in which I explained in
great and logical detail how the telephone companies such as AT&AMP;T
would soon domin
</P>
