A4912 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-GADGETS-HEADPHONES062     06-26 0306
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GADGETS-HEADPHONES0627-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Headphones cancel out unwanted noise
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ A type of noise-canceling stereo headphones
introduced last year for American Airline's international premium
passengers now is available to the general public.
</P>
<P>
   The QuietComfort Acoustic Noise Cancelling headset from Bose is
designed to block or compensate for background noise so the audio
that reaches the listener's ears will be identical to what he would
hear in a quiet room.
</P>
<P>
   The QuietComfort headset reduces noise both physically and
electronically.
</P>
<P>
   The overhead band and arms of the headset are designed to hold
the ear cups over the ears at a natural angle that lets the
listener wear them comfortably for hours. Their padded shell keeps
most noises from reaching the ear.
</P>
<P>
   Inside the ear cups, microphones detect any noise that gets
through the outer shell. The headset then compares that sound to
the desired sound produced by an in-flight movie soundtrack,
portable CD player or other source.
</P>
<P>
   If the microphones detect an unwanted sound, the headset
produces a signal ``opposite'' to the noise to cancel it out.
</P>
<P>
   Passengers in jet aircraft typically experience sound levels
from 75 to 85 decibels, and commuter turboprop planes are even
noisier, according to Bose The National Institute of Occupational
Safety and Health say workers exposed to 85 decibels all day should
wear ear protection.
</P>
<P>
   Bose said the QuietComfort headset lets passengers reach their
destinations more rested and with less stress. QuietComfort
Acoustic Noise Cancelling headsets sell for $299 and can be ordered
direct from Bose by calling (800) 650-2673 (650-BOSE) or visiting
www.bose.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
