   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet PTECH page for the current week. This
layout is now available.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0624 -- An increasing number of car buyers who feel
intimidated by the car-buying process are turning to the Web. More
than a quarter of all used-car shoppers used the Internet for
assistance during the shopping process, according to an August
survey by J.D. Power and Associates. (Ritzler, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes a four-column color photo of a
woman who bought her car via the Web.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: LIST BOX -- A list of sites than can make car buying
easier.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECHNOBUDDY -- Here are some suggestions for using cell
phones in public. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) Art
includes 1 column color sig of columnist.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: GADGETS -- Surround sound takes on an added dimension with
a new Sherwood receiver that offers 6.1 theater sound. (Cummings,
Dayton Daily News) Art includes a 18-pica color photo of receiver.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CYBERSCENE -- Several Web sites teach how to understand
Internet lingo and proper etiquette. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: GAME CORNER -- Perfect Dark for the Nintendo 64 is an
awesome follow-up to the smash hit Goldeneye. (Staff, Austin
American-Statesman) Art includes a 1-column color photo of the box
of Perfect Dark.
</P>
<P>
   END OF COXNET PAGE
</P>
<P>
   GADGETS-HEADPHONES _ DAYTON, Ohio _ A type of noise-canceling
stereo headphones introduced last year for American Airline's
international premium passengers now is available to the general
public. The QuietComfort Acoustic Noise Cancelling headset from
Bose is designed to block or compensate for background noise so the
audio that reaches the listener's ears will be identical to what he
would hear in a quiet room. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). MOVED.
</P>
