r f BC-AUTO-BRIEFS-HNS &LR;      06-26 1092
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AUTO-BRIEFS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     MERCEDES SEDAN TOPS INSURANCE INDUSTRY'S THEFT LIST 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Mercedes-Benz S-class sedan, a large luxury sedan with
equally large prices ($70,000 and up, plus gas-guzzler tax of
$1,000) leads the list of passenger cars that have the highest
insurance losses for theft, according to new figures from the
Highway Loss Data Institute.
</P>
<P>
   The institute, which is supported by the auto insurance
industry, says the S-class' losses from theft are 10 times higher
than the average for all passenger cars.
</P>
<P>
   The S-class has been on list for the past five years, but this
is the first time it has been at the top of the list, the institute
says.
</P>
<P>
   It is also the first time in five years that the annual list of
worst theft losses isn't led by a sport-utility vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Mercedes S-class has appeared on the 10-worst list for
five years, and it's obviously an attractive target for
professional thieves because of its value,'' said Kim Hazelbaker,
the Institute's senior vice president.
</P>
<P>
   Second on this year's list is the two-door Acura Integra, which
has a much lower price tag: It begins at about $20,000. The
four-door Integra is third on the list.
</P>
<P>
   Losses for the Integra are about 10 times worse than the average
among 1997-99 passenger vehicles, the latest report shows.
</P>
<P>
   More Integras are stolen than are Mercedes S-class models, but
the overall losses are higher for the S-class purely because of the
much higher prices, Hazelbaker said.
</P>
<P>
   To help cut Integra thefts, Acura has equipped all 2000 models
with passive anti-theft devices, the institute said.
</P>
<P>
   After the Mercedes, two-door Integra and four-door Integra, the
rest of the top 10, in order, are: the Mitsubishi Montero Sport
four-wheel-drive, Mercedes-Benz SL convertible, Nissan Maxima,
Lexus GS 300/400, BMW 3-series, BMW 7-series long wheelbase, and
Lincoln Navigator four-wheel-drive.
</P>
<P>
   Average loss payments per claim have risen from just over $3,000
in 1980 to about $5,500 in 1999, the institute said. But the 1999
figure is lower than the $5,900 average loss posted for 1998.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   HONDA, GM MODELS ARE `GREEN' MACHINES
</P>
<P>
   The natural-gas powered Honda Civic GX and General Motors' EV1
electric vehicle have been named the year's ``greenest'' vehicles
in updated listings by the American Council for an Energy-Efficient
Economy, which posts the environmental attributes of most cars and
trucks on its GreenerCars.com Web site.
</P>
<P>
   More than 60 new listings have been included in an update to the
site, which now also includes such popular new vehicles as the
Chrysler PT Cruiser and the Volkswagen Passat 4motion sedan.
</P>
<P>
   ``Some of these, like the Passat 4motion, are new configurations
of cars we're already ranking,'' said Jim Kliesch, the council's
research assistant and co-author of the group's annual Green Book,
which is available for purchase through the Web site. ``Others,
like the BMW Z8, are new listings.''
</P>
<P>
   The ratings are updated periodically throughout the year to help
consumers keep up with the continually changing auto market, the
group said.
</P>
<P>
   ``The automotive market is becoming more fluid, with vehicles
being released throughout the year,'' said John DeCicco, lead
author of the Green Book.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our goal is to provide consumers with accurate, up-to-date
environmental information about the cars, trucks and SUVs hitting
the streets today,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   The natural-gas powered Civic GX ties the EV1 with the top
model-year 2000 ``green score'' of 52, he said. Since the current
book went to press, the Civic GX was certified to meet California's
super low emission standard, Kliesch said.
</P>
<P>
   The council's ``green scores'' account for both tailpipe
pollution and global warming impacts, including emissions from auto
factories, petroleum refineries and, for electric vehicles, power
plants.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our posted green scores are based on national average emission
factors,'' Kliesch said. ``In states with cleaner-than-average
electricity generation, such as California, the EV1 would see an
even higher green score.''
</P>
<P>
   In addition to updates of 2000 model-year vehicles, preliminary
analyses of some early 2001 vehicles were performed and posted on
the Web site, the group said. Besides the Passat and the PT
Cruiser, others added during the update include the Acura CL, Ford
Explorer Sport Trac and Oldsmobile Aurora.
</P>
<P>
   ``Green scores of these vehicles will be finalized by early
2001, once the majority of 2001 vehicles are analyzed, but results
are not expected to change significantly,'' DeCicco said.
</P>
<P>
   The Web site is available by paid subscription only, however. If
you want to use it, have your credit card ready.
</P>
<P>
   The print edition of the ``Green Book: The Environmental Guide
to Cars &AMP; Trucks Model Year 2000'' may be ordered through major
on-line booksellers or directly from GreenerCars.com for $8.95 plus
$5 shipping and handling.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   ON-LINE AUTO CONSULTATION
</P>
<P>
   If you're planning to shop for a new Lincoln or Mercury vehicle
and you have a personal computer at your disposal, Ford's Lincoln
Mercury division wants to hook you up with a ``personal
consultant'' to help explain everything you might want to know
about the vehicle you are considering.
</P>
<P>
   In a first for the auto industry, the Lincoln Mercury on-line
personal consultant service began in June on both the
Lincolnvehicles.com and Mercuryvehicles.com Web sites.
</P>
<P>
   There, a consultant is available to communicate directly with
potential buyers, to allow consumers to get product information,
arrange a test drive, obtain a price quote and even arrange for
delivery of the vehicle from the consumer's dealer of choice,
Lincoln Mercury officials said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Shopping for a new vehicle online can be difficult and
stressful,'' said Harlan Lassen, Lincoln Mercury's Internet
manager. ``We believe our personal consultants, by adding the human
touch, can make buying a car online a more enjoyable experience.''
</P>
<P>
   The service is staffed by Lincoln Mercury product specialists,
who communicate via e-mail, including real-time chat, or by
telephone, in English or Spanish. They promise to respond to all
requests within 24 hours, and there is no charge for the service.
</P>
<P>
   The product specialists do not earn commissions from any sales,
Ford says.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
