<HEADER>
A5201 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u e BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS &LR;      06-26 0413
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`SWEET AND LOWDOWN' A LOVABLE ROMANCE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Sweet and Lowdown'' (DVD) _ Sean Penn is
perfectly cast as a jazz guitarist in Woody Allen's finely wrought
comedy. Set in the 1930s, this lovable romance also features fine
performances by Gretchen Mol and Samantha Morton. Criticized as
``light'' Woody Allen, this pleasant movie actually expands the
writer-director's range.
</P>
<P>
   ``Anna and the King'' _ ``The King and I'' without the music.
Beautifully directed with rich colors and pageantry, but the story
is outdated and silly. No Rodgers. No Hammerstein. No movie.
</P>
<P>
   ``Topsy-Turvy'' (DVD) _ Director Mike Leigh does a remarkable
job with the story of librettist W. S. Gilbert and composer Arthur
Sullivan. It's an amusing behind-the-scenes story of the making of
``The Mikado,'' with the omnipresent British class system making
for a most suitable backstory.
</P>
<P>
   ``Liberty Heights'' _ Director Barry Levinson continues his
affectionate memoir of growing up in Baltimore during the 1950s,
with mixed results. It's an even-tempered, nostalgic trip _ but the
problem is that Levinson led off the series with his best film,
``Diner.'' The ones that followed just don't match up.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   VSDA SAYS NO TO RATINGS BILL: In a move that shouldn't surprise
anyone, the Video Software Dealers Association opposes legislation
before Congress that would require all home videos and video games
to carry a label categorizing the level of violence and setting age
restrictions on their products. VSDA president Bo Andersen told
Video Business magazine that the bill is ``unquestionably
unconstitutional and unnecessary.'' Andersen also pointed out
various groups, including Pledge to Parents, already review and
advise parents on the suitability of films and games for children.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: June 27: ``The Talented Mr. Ripley'' (DVD),
``Runaway Bride'' (DVD). July 5: ``Scream 3'' (DVD), ``Divine
Trash'' (DVD), ``Santitos.'' July 11: ``The Hurricane'' (DVD),
``All About My Mother'' (DVD), ``Boiler Room,'' ``My Dog Skip''
(DVD), ``Jaws'' (DVD), ``The Fourth Floor,'' ``Mansfield Park.''
July 18: ``Ride With the Devil,'' ``What Planet Are You From?''
(DVD), ``Identification of a Woman,'' ``Angela's Ashes,''
