Stacey Augmon at No. 9. Neither player made a huge impact and got
released or traded. But the biggest problem: 1985. The Hawks took
Jon Koncak at No. 5 and missed out on the following players: Karl
Malone, Chris Mullin, Detleft Schrempf and Charles Oakley. A look
at both hits and misses on draft day. (Denberg, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
