<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-ELECTION (Ciudad Victoria, Mexico) _ In the northern
border state of Tamaulipas, one of the world's longest surviving
and well oiled political machines uses threats, gifts, fake
nonprofit groups and intricate, pyramid-style organizing to nail
down votes. By Richard Chacon. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   ZIMBABWE-BALLOTS (Nhedziwa, Zimbabwe) _ As the nation awaits the
official ballot tally, which begins Monday, anecdotal evidence
suggests the race card didn't work that well for President Robert
Mugabe. By Kurt Shillinger. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-VOTE (Tokyo) _ Japan's gaffe-prone prime minister, Yoshiro
