<P>
   BLUE DENIM NEVER GOES OUT OF STYLE
</P>
<P>
   DENIM-LIFEBEAT _ Denim has been produced in the United States
since late in the 18th century, but it was Bavarian-born
businessman Levi Strauss who, in 1873, made it an American icon.
Initially embraced by miners, farmers and other manual laborers,
blue jeans came to symbolize the swaggering American cowboy during
the 1930s. Eventually, Hollywood movie stars turned blue jeans into
a uniform. Today, vintage jeans can sell for as much as $10,000 and
denim is being used to make everything from tote bags to home
accessories of all kinds. By Debra Muller Price.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos of denim garments and accessories available in
JPEG format by calling William Gonzalez at 212-499-3355.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FEAR OF FLYING? FLIGHT PHOBIA CAN BE TREATED WITH VIRTUAL
REALITY
</P>
<P>
   FLIGHT-FEAR-LIFEBEAT_ Some people are so afraid of flying that
it limits their career options, keeps them from visiting family and
friends or causes them to tremble and hyperventilate every time
they have to step on a plane. Many of these ``fearful flyers'' may
be able to find help with an unusual treatment called ``virtual
reality exposure therapy.'' In a therapist's suite, patients watch
a 3-D animated movie on a computer, complete with the sights,
sounds and vibrations of flying. It's the closest thing to being
there. Increasingly available through mental health practitioners
and clinics, this therapy is helping some people overcome their
fear of flying. By Shawn O'Leary.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos of an airplane and of someone receiving virtual
reality therapy are available in JPEG format by calling William
Gonzalez at 212-499-3355.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   VEGETARIAN A, B, C'S
</P>
<P>
   VEGETARIANISM-NUTRITION-LIFEBEAT _ Each year roughly one million
people become vegetarians. Many of these newcomers do so in simple
fashion, forking their steak aside to dine on the remaining
garnishes; potato salad, a roll or three and a bowl of lettuce
backstroking in dressing. Happy news if you have stock in starch
and fat, bad news if you are the one eating like this. While there
are good reasons to move toward what experts call a
``plant-centered'' diet, the more restrictive the diet, the more
people need to think about their food choices. Being misinformed
can lead to deficiencies and serious problems. By Ken McAlpine.
</P>
<P>
   MORE THAN JUST A PRETTY POSY, ROSES CAN HEAL BODY AND SOUL
</P>
<P>
   ROSES-ALTERNATIVE-MEDICINE-LIFEBEAT _ Roses, which have been
cultivated for thousands of years, are associated with love and
purity, but they are practical as well as beautiful and symbolic.
By the beginning of the 18th century, American colonists were using
roses for wines, dyes, medicines, pomanders, potpourris,
confections, perfumes and oils. Rose petals and hips steeped in tea
are said to bring down fevers and clear toxins out of the body,
while some people use rose syrup to relieve sore throats and rose
water to cure headaches and tighten sagging skin. By Maggy Howe.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: A photo of a rose is available in JPEG format by
calling William Gonzalez at 212-499-3355.) &QL;
</P>
