to put truckers on a 24-hourcycle rather than a 16-hour cycle and
to require two-day rest periods. Truckers are up in arms, say ing
it will require more trucks on the roads, driver shortages, lower
incomes, etc. Safety advocates also oppose the plan. There'll be a
public hearing on the proposed rules next Friday. (Grantham,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
