<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0624 -- An increasing number of car buyers who feel
intimidated by the car-buying process are turning to the Web. More
than a quarter of all used-car shoppers used the Internet for
assistance during the shopping process, according to an August
survey by J.D. Power and Associates. (Ritzler, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes a four-column color photo of a
woman who bought her car via the Web.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: LIST BOX -- A list of sites than can make car buying
easier.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECHNOBUDDY -- Here are some suggestions for using cell
phones in public. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) Art
includes 1 column color sig of columnist.
