</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-MLBPROBE _ ATLANTA _ Major League Baseball is looking
into the catcher's box controversy with the Braves at Turner Field
over the weekend. And TBS' use of superimposed images to show what
appeared to be an effort to skirt the rules by the Braves, results
in the TBS team being kicked off the Braves charter for this road
trip (ROgers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-ROADTRIP _ ATLANTA _ The Braves are not sure what to
expect on the trip that begins in Montreal on Tuesday then winds
into New York. But the players are trying to distance themselves
from the John Rocker vs. New York issue. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-SOSA-VOTES _ Your NL votes for Sammy Sosa won't be wasted if
he's traded to an AL team before the All-Star game on July 11.
Commissioner Bud Selig says the votes will go with him and he would
qualify for the AL team. Voting ends Tuesday at ballparks, but
continues on the internet through the weekend with internet curbs
in place to prevent someone from voting too many times. (Curtright,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKN-HAWKS-HIGHPICKS _ ATLANTA _ The Hawks, who have the sixth
overall pick in Wednesday's draft, haven't had much success with
high picks. The last time they had a lottery choice, it was used
for Adam Keefe of Stanford in 1992. The year before, they chose
Stacey Augmon at No. 9. Neither player made a huge impact and got
released or traded. But the biggest problem: 1985. The Hawks took
Jon Koncak at No. 5 and missed out on the following players: Karl
Malone, Chris Mullin, Detleft Schrempf and Charles Oakley. A look
at both hits and misses on draft day. (Denberg, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
