<P>
   BONNIE AND CLYDE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Sixty-six years after they died in a backwoods ambush,
Clyde Barrow and Bonnie Parker remain folk heroes. The outlaw duo
wasn't nearly as glamorous as legend would have it, but their lives
_ and deaths _ were certainly colorful. Several sites of
significance in their criminal careers are within easy driving
distance of Dallas-Fort Worth, and eyewitnesses still remain who
can help tell the ``real'' story of Bonnie and Clyde. By JEFF
GUINN. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CANCER SURVIVOR-MED STUDENT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ After three surgeries followed by chemotherapy to
treat osteosarcoma _ a rare bone cancer afflicting adolescents _
Kurt Weiss was told that nothing more could be done. But Weiss'
sister saw an article about an experimental treatment for
osteosarcoma that was being tested by Dr. Eugenie Kleinerman at the
M.D. Anderson Cancer center in Houston. Weiss became part of the
doctor's trial testing of a new drug, MTP. Ten years later, Weiss
is cancer-free. He is also a medical student, who worked
side-by-side with Kleinerman last summer as she continued her
cancer research. By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES. Story will move in ``l''
lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNCERTAIN-SEARCH &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNCERTAIN, Texas _ A woman's search for the sunken wreck of a
paddle-wheel steamer in swampy Lake Caddo takes unexpected turns in
the moss-draped bayous of East Texas. By JESSIE MILLIGAN. Story
will move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
