<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Finally, after all the propaganda and all the protests
and all the posturing by Gary Graham and his partisans, Graham got
what he deserved. Having avoided execution for 19 years with an
endless stream of groundless appeals, Graham managed to delay
justice another two hours and 49 minutes Thursday as his lawyers
launched a last, desperate round of court filings. In the end,
though, the cause of law and order prevailed. By BILL THOMPSON.
Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
