   SMITH-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LAGUNA ATASCOSA NATIONAL WILDLIFE REFUGE, Texas _ Early on a
June morning, you can walk for miles here without seeing another
human being. But you'll likely see whitetail deer, cottontail
rabbits, roadrunners, Texas tortoises and colorful birds ranging
from green jays to roseate spoonbills. You might even spot an
American alligator or make a rare sighting of an ocelot. By JACK Z.
SMITH. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
