motivated by bias and therefore subject to an increased maximum
sentence. (O'Dell, Cox News Service). 15.
</P>
<P>
   DAVIDIAN-TRIAL27 _ WACO, Texas _ Davidian Marjorie Thomas
testifies about fleeing the fire on April 19, 1993, almost
stumbling over the body of Sheila Martin's daughter. Thomas said
the Davidians did not plan to commit suicide. However, she also
told a government attorney that the Davidians had once planned to
commit suicide during the siege by blowing themselves up with hand
grenades, but David Koresh called it off. (England, Waco
Tribune-Herald). 25.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-SURPLUS _ WASHINGTON _ President Clinton announced
Monday that the U.S. budget surplus would likely hit $1.87 trillion
by 2010, more than twice the surplus estimated four months ago.
Clinton coupled the announcement with an offer to Republican
congressional leaders to sign a bill cutting taxes for married
couples by $250 billion over10 years if they accept his plan to
provide prescription drugs coverage under Medicare. (Deans, Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   PASSENGER-RIGHTS _ WASHINGTON _ The U.S. government releases
Tuesday its first assessment of a voluntary passenger service
reform plan by airlines. The U.S. Transportation Department's
inspector general is expected to givst in ramming techniques. (Waco
Tribune-Herald). 12.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY _ HUNSTVILLE, Texas _ It was only 100 yards that
separated opponents and proponents of the execution of Gary Graham
outside the Texas prison in Huntsville last week. Yet, the separate
groups were divided by a world of difference. (Joe Murray, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio. _ ``Got any rhubarb?'' Gene
is asking Cal as I pick up my morning cup of decaf and take it to
the empty seat between them. ``I'll trade you lettuce for some
rhubarb.'' Cal squints, nods and smiles. Being a newcomer, Gene
thinks this means he's got himself a deal but that's not it. It
means Cal hasn'ols to get jobs done. (Cleere/Rudd, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
