<P>
   ARCHITECT-HOUSEWARES _ Michael Graves already was pretty famous,
at least in design circles. And now that he's created a line of
housewares for Target, the internationally-acclaimed architect has
become a household name. Just don't think at 65, Graves holds any
qualms about his art, including some 600 pieces, being marketed by
a discount retailer. He's just happy the masses are finally being
exposed to cool design. It's a lesson the architect, whose projects
include Atlanta's Carlos Museum renovation, will deliver on Tuesday
in Atlanta to the Georgia chapter of the American Association of
Interior Designers. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
