   WHERE I-BUSINESS IS CONCERNED, HONEYWELL IS JUST GETTING STARTED
</P>
<P>
   BC-ECOM-HONEYWELL _ The Internet has become a miraculous
storehouse of information, a vast electronic mall, a link to Wall
Street. But for all the excitement over the prospect of an Internet
connection in every home, this is not where the big money is. What
companies spend buying and selling goods and services to one
another dwarfs consumer spending. The score last year was $14
trillion to $3 trillion. Here, a report on how large companies,
such as the industrial manufacturer Honeywell Inc., are beginning
to shift intercompany sales to the Internet. By Louis Uchitelle.
WITH PHOTOS.
