<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 18:37 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5449 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l BC-UNCERTAIN-SEARCH-2ndT     06-26 0681
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-UNCERTAIN-SEARCH-2ndTake-TEX </SLUG>
 
UNCERTAIN, Texas: 61, says. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The incorporation papers were returned to him because he had
written ``Uncertain'' on the line of the form asking for the name
of the city. Smith sent the papers back with an explanation, and
the new city of Uncertain was born as a place with better tap water
and a more certain chance of finding a beer.
</P>
<P>
   Today, Uncertain is home to about 200 people, mostly artists
specializing in lake scenes, fishing guides, and bed and breakfast
owners. The city limits encompass a narrow stretch of lakeshore.
Uncertain is not more than a few blocks wide and about a mile long.
Residents, including the founder's daughter, Dottie Carter, worry
that someday the chain fast-food places and motels will arrive, but
that hasn't happened yet. The city does not feel like a city. Its
Main Street is really the lake, where all of life is focused. Set
back from the lakeshore, where the pines meet the cypress trees, is
Uncertain City Hall and the Uncertain Volunteer Fire Department.
There is no Uncertain Search and Rescue, although tourists become
confused when out on the maze of channels that make up the lake.
Sometimes, uncertain about how to return to Uncertain, they don't
come back until very late at night.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   In the early 1970s, Palmore got a job as a maid aboard the Delta
Queen riverboat that takes tourists out on the Ohio and Mississippi
rivers. She spent so much time in the pilot house trying to learn
the river that she cleaned rooms only seven months before the
company paid for her to attend a school where riverboat pilots are
trained.
</P>
<P>
   She steered the Delta Queen about five years, then left the
river but brought along her love of steamboats.
</P>
<P>
   She returned to her Tyler home, but eventually headed to
Uncertain to look for Mittie Stephens artifacts. If she found
pieces of the boat, she'd be able to use more accurate historical
detail in her oil paintings of steamboats. She loves the boats, the
way the paddle wheels splash through the bayous without the sound
of a motor to ruin the mood.
</P>
<P>
   It's easy to fall under the spell of Uncertain. Whether it's
miasma or charm, something about the quiet lake with shadowy
channels and deep shade makes a person want to stay.
</P>
<P>
   So, even after no sign of the Mittie Stephens, Palmore stayed
on, absorbing the slow-placed life on the lake.
</P>
<P>
   She'd paint signs for businesses, and while she did, she also
commissioned the building of a historically accurate reproduction
of a riverboat, as near as she could tell. She calls the
50-foot-long paddle-wheel boat the Graceful Ghost, after an old
piece of music she says is beautiful. She intended the boat to be
her home, but eventually she began using it as a moneymaker, taking
Uncertain tourists out for rides.
</P>
<P>
   On summer evenings she and her husband, Jim McMillen, 57, offer
the tours. It's quiet, except for the chorus of frogs somewhere
beyond the long shadows that come before sunset. Palmore watches
the shifting light on the water.
</P>
<P>
   She recalls the fish that looked so surprised after it had
jumped out of the water and landed on a lily pad. She sees the
iridescent blue dragonflies light on a pale yellow American lotus
flower floating in the lake. She remembers the way waves from the
paddlewheel cause shimmery droplets of lake to roll across the lily
pads, and the way the cypress turns rust-colored in the fall. She
looks for the red-eared sliders, which she hears are being caught
by poachers who send females to Asia for a turtle-egg market.
She'll paint a red-eared slider some day.
</P>
<P>
   Some day, maybe she'll get back to looking for the Mittie
Stephens. She isn't sure. For now, like many of the other artistic
residents of this town who are drawn to the lake, she is mesmerized
by its primordial beauty and is drawn to paint it.
</P>
<P>
   Although she came to the lake with a certain goal, the aura of
the lake has seemed to capture her, anchoring her here, as it does,
in an Uncertain spot.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
