   EXP-FED (Washington) _ After a period of rip-roaring growth that
fueled fears of inflation, the economy is showing enough signs of
slowing that the Federal Reserve will most likely leave interest
rate policy unchanged when it meets on Tuesday and Wednesday,
economists and analysts say. But as it looks ahead, the Fed faces
two big question marks that might lead it to go back to raising
interest rates later in the year. By Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
