   CHINA-TAIWAN (Taipei, Taiwan) _ Ask Stan Shih about personal
computers, the Internet or his native Taiwan, and he holds forth
enthusiastically. Not for nothing is Shih, the voluble founder of
the computer maker Acer, regarded as the head cheerleader and
unofficial spokesman for corporate Taiwan. But ask Shih whether he
favors an independent Taiwan, and he turns monosyllabic. ``No,'' he
says, as his Cheshire-cat smile tightens. By Mark Landler.
</P>
