deal to sell off Nabisco: Philip Morris shareholders, who saw the
price of their stock rise nearly $4 Monday, and Carl Icahn, the
value investor whose betting against the market when he bought a
stake in Nabisco Group Holdings gave him a very large psychic and
financial victory. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
