<HEADLINE>
HOT TRAVEL DEALS 
</HEADLINE>
  (For release Sunday, July 20 
 &HT;     
 By JANET PIORKO    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   COMBO TICKETS _ Admission to three attractions in Greater
Cleveland _ the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and Museum, Six Flags
Ohio and SeaWorld _ is combined in a Wild Thing ticket that costs
$49.95; $39.95 for children under 48 inches tall. Tickets, valid
through the Labor Day weekend, are on sale at the three sites as
well as in the visitor information center of the Convention and
Visitors Bureau of Greater Cleveland, in the city's Flats
entertainment district along the Cuyahoga River. The regular
combined admission is $79.77, and $52.63 for children. The Rock and
Roll Hall of Fame is in downtown Cleveland; SeaWorld and Six Flags
are in Aurora, about 25 miles southeast. Information: (877)
937-9453.
</P>
<P>
   CEZANNE CHARTERED _ EuroCruises, a New York company, has
chartered the 49-cabin riverboat Cezanne for a seven-night cruise
out of Avignon on the Rhone and Saone Rivers, priced from $2,150 a
person, double, with air fare on Continental between Newark and
Paris, and the train to Avignon. Cabins have two convertible sofa
beds (except six queen-size cabins with a queen bed and separate
couch, at $2,850) and air-conditioning. Shore tours, $35 to $100,
include Arles and Beaujolais. Information: (800) 688-3876 or
www.eurocruises.com.
</P>
<P>
   CARIBBEAN SUMMER _ Promotions abound in the Caribbean at this
time of year, for travelers willing to take a chance with the
weather. (Hurricane season is typically at its peak from mid-August
to mid-October.) Among the discounts:
</P>
<P>
   The Elegant Hotels Group offers five nights for the price of
four at its five Barbados properties, ranging from the 166-room
Tamarind Cove Hotel, where a double starts at $258, to the 167-room
Turtle Beach Resort, where $490 a night buys an ocean-view junior
suite with meals, drinks and some activities such as snorkeling.
Two children under 12 can stay in the room with their parents at no
extra charge at all resorts except Coconut Creek. Good through Dec.
18; call (800) 326-6898.
</P>
<P>
   The Hyatt Regency St. Lucia, which opened in April, is offering
50 percent off regular rates through Sept. 30; discounted prices
start at $112.50 a night and must be booked by July 31. The
284-room resort, on a 1,000-foot beach, is six miles from Castries
on the causeway to Pigeon Island. It has two lighted tennis courts,
three restaurants and bars, a spa and water sports; (800) 233-1234.
</P>
<P>
   At the Wyndham El Conquistador in Puerto Rico, an ocean-view
room with access to the adjacent Golden Door Spa is $225 a person
per night, double occupancy, through Dec. 18; the package includes
tax, full breakfast and choice of a 50-minute spa treatment or a
round of golf daily; there is a three-day minimum stay. The resort,
on a bluff overlooking the Atlantic, about 45 minutes' drive east
of San Juan, has six swimming pools and a casino. Call (800)
996-3426.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
