<SLUG> BC-BBN-LOPEZ-COLUMN-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Astros could use some comic relief
<TEXT>
<P>
   By JOHN P. LOPEZ
</P>
<P>
   Houston Chronicle
</P>
<P>
   What if, in a bold attempt to follow up on ABC's recent decision
to put comedian Dennis Miller in the booth for Monday Night
Football broadcasts, the Astros did the same?
</P>
<P>
   What if in hopes of juicing up this hellish season, an array of
comedians past and present, gone-but-not-forgotten voices as well
as current stars, could join Milo Hamilton in the radio booth?
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``Welcome to the Astros Radio Network. With me today is
Bob `There's Still' Hope. There is still hope, isn't there, Bob?''
</P>
<P>
   Hope: ``No, there's not. Actually, not one of the `On The Road'
films I made was as bad as what the Astros have done on the road
this year. Home isn't so hot, either. I've visited troops in Da
Nang that had less of a 1,000-yard stare on their faces than some
of these guys with the bases loaded and nobody out.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to tell ya, if the tabloids think I'm the one on life
support, they ought to go to Enron Field some time.''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``Well, how bad is it? Hey, heeeere's Johnny!''
</P>
<P>
   Johnny Carson: ``This Astros season is so bad Magic Johnson had
a better run on late-night TV. Billy Ray Cyrus had more hits.
Pee-wee Herman never struck out in clutch situations this often.''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry Seinfeld: ``Sure he did. Want to have a contest?''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``What kind of contest?''
</P>
<P>
   Seinfeld: ``Let's you and I not order room service on the road
until the Astros can win three in a row.''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``I think the Astros will win that one. But really, what's
the biggest problem with this team right now? How would you
describe it?''
</P>
<P>
   Sam Kinison: ``AAAwwwooh. Aaawwooh. Aawwooh!!!''
</P>
<P>
   Chris Rock: ``%$&AMP;. $%&AMP;. %!''
</P>
<P>
   Richard Pryor: ``&AMP;%$. &AMP;$. %$!''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``Why don't we ask someone else? How would you describe
it, Henny?''
</P>
<P>
   Henny Youngman: ``Take the pitching staff . . . please!''
</P>
<P>
   Rodney Dangerfield: ``I tell you, the Astros don't get no
respect.''
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Foxworthy: ``You know, you might be an Astro if the only
thing juicier than a big hunk o' Spam on the plate is one of your
fastballs.
</P>
<P>
   ``You might be an Astro if you strike out looking three times
with runners in scoring position. You might be an Astro if you've
gone from the penthouse to a trailer park in the path of a twister
in less than nine months.
</P>
<P>
   ``You might be a new-and-not-so-improved Astro if pictures of
Cindy Crawford and Morgan Fairchild that once hung in the clubhouse
have been replaced with pictures of Britney Spears and Christina
Aguilera. You might be an Astro if all the peach fuzz on the new
faces still doesn't add up to the hair on Ken Caminiti's goatee.''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``You might be right. Hey, there's a long fly ball off
Jose Lima . . . back, back, gone. Holy Toledo!''
</P>
<P>
   Drew Carey: ``Don't you mean, `Holy Cleveland?'''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``Look, you've got your favorite city in Ohio; I've got
mine. Whose line is it, anyway?''
</P>
<P>
   Steve Martin: ``That Lima, he's one wild and crazy guy!''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``Yeah, but he's 1-11. What's that Larry Dierker is
shouting down there in the dugout?''
</P>
<P>
   George Carlin: ``I think it's the seven words you can't say on
television.''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``Do you read lips?''
</P>
<P>
   Roseanne: ``No, but if you hum a few bars, I'll sing the
national anthem.''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``Uh, no. Things haven't gotten that bad yet.''
</P>
<P>
   David Letterman: ``Sure, they have. In fact, here are the Top 10
reasons things have gone so wrong for the Astros this season:
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 10 _ No Dome dogs.
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 9 _ Pinstripes only work for the Yankees.
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 8 _ The last time I spent $5.25 for a beer, Charles
Barkley was at the table next to me with a fistful of dollar bills.
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 7 _ Jeff Bagwell should have kept the Capt. Lou Albano
beard.
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 6 _ Jose Lima lost his mojo.
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 5 _ We need the other Maddux!
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 4 _ Two words: Casey Candaele.
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 3 _ That's baseball.
</P>
<P>
   ``No. 2 _ Another division banner would cover up all the
advertising in the outfield.
</P>
<P>
   ``And the No. 1 reason things have gone so wrong for the Astros
this season: How can you expect them to get into contention when
they can't even get onto the Internet? That requires putting three
W's together.''
</P>
<P>
   George Burns: ``Say goodnight, Astros.''
</P>
<P>
   Milo: ``Goodnight, Astros.''
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
